        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "FWIW here is the code I hacked together to do this myself. Not to say it should be implemented exactly like this, but hopefully it is useful when this actually gets implemented somewhere.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom itertools import product, starmap\r\nfrom operator import methodcaller\r\n\r\nimport numpy as np\r\n\r\nfrom dask.array import Array\r\nfrom dask.base import tokenize\r\nfrom dask.core import flatten\r\nfrom dask.highlevelgraph import HighLevelGraph\r\n\r\n\r\ndef ravel_chunks(arr):\r\n    name = \"ravel_chunks-\" + tokenize(arr)\r\n    chunks = (tuple(map(np.product, product(*a.chunks))),)\r\n    dsk = {(name, i): (methodcaller(\"ravel\"), k)\r\n           for i, k in enumerate(flatten(arr.__dask_keys__()))}\r\n    graph = HighLevelGraph.from_collections(name, dsk, dependencies=[arr])\r\n    res = Array(graph, name, chunks, arr.dtype)\r\n    \r\n    return res\r\n```",
