        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "For the question you actually asked:\r\n1. I'd also vote no for option 3 (I agree with @shoyer on this, he explains the potential pitfalls well upthread). \r\n2. I'd want to prioritise an API that is compatible with numpy as far as possible. Ideally it would be relatively easy for users to take code they wrote for dask arrays and re-use it for numpy arrays without it breaking. In cases where that's not possible, maybe it's best to try and make things obviously non-compatible with numpy? Would that help narrow down the remaining options?\r\n\r\nMy thinking around point 2 is very fuzzy, so I'd welcome anyone else expanding on these points or arguing against them.\r\n\r\n",
