        "body": "> 2\\. I'd want to prioritise an API that is compatible with numpy as far as possible. Ideally it would be relatively easy for users to take code they wrote for dask arrays and re-use it for numpy arrays without it breaking. In cases where that's not possible, maybe it's best to try and make things obviously non-compatible with numpy? Would that help narrow down the remaining options?\r\n\r\nI strongly agree with this. Given the negative impact of option 3, that only leaves us with option 4, which wouldn't meddle with NumPy API at all.\r\n\r\nThat said, my vote remains for option 4.",
